[link: #table-of-contents] ’Щ@d08a348bfbf846a8f304e0f47e915b621cdf1c09a7aa4ce1a2ead9fe61cc714fЪ‘Title: title: Nushell 0.105.1
Path: ]
Content:
``coreutils``
``cargo install``
[link: #table-of-contents] Bumping 
``coreutils``
 to 0.1.0 broke 
``cargo install nu``
.

The new version requires the 
``PROJECT_NAME_FOR_VERSION_STRING``
 environment variable at build time, which we had set in our 
``.cargo/config.toml``
.
Unfortunately, 
``cargo publish``
 does 
not
 ignore that file, which is considered 
[link: https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/issues/14001] a bug in Cargo
.

As a result, we published a version that couldn't be installed without setting that env var manually.
[link: https://github.com/uutils/coreutils/issues/7992] The 
``coreutils``
 team is running into this too
.
For now, we've reverted 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15896] #15896
 in 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15932] #15932
.

We'll bump 
``coreutils``
 again once theyвЂ™ve sorted out a fix.
